-- Haraguchi Aims to Cut Japan Civil Servant Numbers by 60,000, Yomiuri Says
-- Yoshiaki Nohara
-- 2010-07-25T01:39:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/haraguchi-aims-to-cut-japan-civil-servant-numbers-by-60-000-yomiuri-says.html

          
          
             Japanese Internal Affairs Minister
Kazuhiro Haraguchi said yesterday he aims to cut the number of
civil servants by 60,000, the Yomiuri newspaper reported today.
The cuts will be made by attrition and reducing new hiring,
Haraguchi said.  
